table.operations

Class GroupOps

  • java.lang.Object
    • table.operations.GroupOps
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableOperationInterface

    public class GroupOps
extends Object
implements TableOperationInterface
    The GroupOps class is an operation for the MyTable.runOp() function. It creates a new table where repeated elements in the specified column are grouped together. The provided ops are then run separately for each of the grouped rows. Similar to the SQL 'GROUP BY' statement. The getResult() method of the GroupOps class returns value returns a MyTable object.
    Author:
    Saud Fatayerji
